The paper addresses the problem of vehicle self-localization using multi-modal sensor information and a reference map, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed solution involves using a deep neural network to regress the vehicle's translation and rotation parameters from input landmarks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of synthetic ground-truth during training, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the proposed approach can be combined with filtering algorithms, which is relevant to control systems (cs.SY).
